RIYADH: Makkah Gov. Prince Khaled Al-Faisal received the ambassador of Qatar to the Kingdom, Bandar bin Mohammed Al-Attiyah, in Makkah on Sunday. During the meeting, they exchanged cordial conversation and discussed issues of common interest. Recently, Al-Attiyah presented his credentials as his country’s permanent representative to the Organization of Islamic Cooperation to Hissein Brahim Taha, the OIC’s secretary-general, in Jeddah. During their meeting, they also reviewed relations and cooperation between the OIC and Qatar, along with other issues of common interest. Earlier, the Qatari envoy also met Riyadh Gov. Prince Faisal bin Bandar bin Abdulaziz, and the pair also discussed issues of common interest.